File: A healthcare worker prepares a COVID-19 test. AFP/Luca Sola JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is seeing an increase in the number of new COVID-19 infections. The Health Department reported 2,759 new COVID-19 cases in the last 24 hours. READ: COVID-19 outbreak at elite Joburg school However, the department says SA is not yet experiencing a third wave of infections. A total of 72 more confirmed deaths takes the COVID-19 death toll to 54,968 The recovery rate remains at 95 percent. So far, 430,730 health workers are vaccinated. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 12 May.
